Use the standard library
This is how to prod_signs of arr:
   Remember that n is arr's length
   When n is 0, then:
      The answer is []
   End when
   Remember that product is 1
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that x is item i in arr
      When x is 0, then:
         The answer is [0]
      End when
      When x is less than 0, then:
         Remember that product is diff of 0 and product
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that result is diff of 0 and (product of 9 and product)
   The answer is [result]
Now you know